00:36:47,762 --> 00:36:49,294
I'm glad you like it.

972
00:36:49,330 --> 00:36:51,764
I don't just like it.
I love it.

973
00:36:51,799 --> 00:36:53,632
Just like I love you.

974
00:36:53,667 --> 00:36:57,136
<i>[tense music]</i>

975
00:36:57,788 --> 00:36:59,087
Oh, Tara, I love you--

976
00:36:59,123 --> 00:37:01,323
- What?
- It.

977
00:37:01,358 --> 00:37:03,258
Your idea...what you were
talking about earlier.

978
00:37:03,293 --> 00:37:04,593
- Which idea?
- What happened?

979
00:37:04,628 --> 00:37:05,705
Louis, are you okay?
[door opens]

980
00:37:05,729 --> 00:37:08,130
What the hell
is going on here?

981
00:37:08,697 --> 00:37:09,763
Nothing's going on here.

982
00:37:09,798 --> 00:37:10,975
What the hell are you doing
in my house?

983
00:37:10,999 --> 00:37:12,766
- Your house?
- Louis, who are these people?

984
00:37:12,801 --> 00:37:14,568
These people are
the registered owners

985
00:37:14,603 --> 00:37:16,303
of this property.

986
00:37:16,338 --> 00:37:17,871
You mean the one you said
had been

987
00:37:17,906 --> 00:37:19,139
in your family
for generations?

988
00:37:19,174 --> 00:37:21,274
That's a lie.
We built this house ourselves,

989
00:37:21,310 --> 00:37:25,712
and until five minutes ago,
we were gonna sell it to him.

990
00:37:25,747 --> 00:37:27,380
Tara, I can explain.

991
00:37:27,416 --> 00:37:30,150
I don't need you to explain.
I've heard enough.

992
00:37:30,185 --> 00:37:33,220
Tara, wait.
Please.

993
00:37:33,864 --> 00:37:35,063
Tara, please wait.

994
00:37:35,098 --> 00:37:37,766
You know, I've heard
about people like you.

995
00:37:37,801 --> 00:37:39,479
You're trying to get free
design work out of me,

996
00:37:39,503 --> 00:37:42,070
so you can decide whether or not
you want to buy this house.

997
00:37:42,263 --> 00:37:43,374
That has nothing
to do with it.

998
00:37:43,398 --> 00:37:44,964
Really?
Because, first,

999
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:46,077
you tried to get me
to work on this

1000
00:37:46,101 --> 00:37:47,633
without even seeing the space.

1001
00:37:47,669 --> 00:37:49,413
Then you lured me out here
under false pretenses.

1002
00:37:49,437 --> 00:37:52,138
So why don't you tell me what,
exactly, is going on here?

1003
00:37:52,173 --> 00:37:53,818
I lied to you about owning
a house in the Hamptons

1004
00:37:53,842 --> 00:37:56,509
so I could spend time
with you.

1005
00:37:57,101 --> 00:37:59,535
What?
Why--why would you do that?

1006
00:37:59,571 --> 00:38:03,372
Because you are perfect,
and beautiful,

1007
00:38:03,408 --> 00:38:06,509
and intelligent,
and talented,

1008
00:38:06,544 --> 00:38:10,346
and so far out of my league.

1009
00:38:10,381 --> 00:38:12,915
It was the only thing that I can
come up with to find the time

1010
00:38:12,951 --> 00:38:15,751
I needed to make you
fall for me.

1011
00:38:15,954 --> 00:38:17,887
You were willing to buy
and remodel

1012
00:38:17,922 --> 00:38:21,591
- an entire house to do that?
- I was.

1013
00:38:22,108 --> 00:38:26,911
That's the most romantic thing
I've ever heard.

1014
00:38:26,946 --> 00:38:28,813
Really?

1015
00:38:28,848 --> 00:38:32,950
Yeah. Yes, really.
[chuckles]

1016
00:38:32,986 --> 00:38:36,053
Tara, would you like
to have dinner with me?

1017
00:38:36,089 --> 00:38:38,489
I'd love to, Louis.

1018
00:38:38,524 --> 00:38:41,726
- [chuckles]
- Yeah.

1019
00:38:41,761 --> 00:38:44,695
<i>[soft music]</i>

1020
00:38:48,601 --> 00:38:50,601
What are you working on?

1021
00:38:51,110 --> 00:38:53,777
An engagement letter.

1022
00:38:53,812 --> 00:38:54,878
You got a new client.

1023
00:38:54,913 --> 00:38:57,714
I got us two new clients.

1024
00:38:57,750 --> 00:38:59,850
So that's what you had
to do the other day.

1025
00:38:59,885 --> 00:39:01,518
Well, something like that.

1026
00:39:01,553 --> 00:39:04,888
The one I got the other day
led to the one I got today.

1027
00:39:04,923 --> 00:39:06,490
That's great.

1028
00:39:06,525 --> 00:39:09,493
Yeah, what's on your mind?

1029
00:39:11,563 --> 00:39:12,907
I know you said that you'd
give me

1030
00:39:12,931 --> 00:39:15,065
an hour of your time
later this week,

1031
00:39:15,100 --> 00:39:17,167
but I need that hour tonight.

1032
00:39:17,202 --> 00:39:18,769
Rachel, it's been a long day.

1033
00:39:18,804 --> 00:39:20,181
Can we talk about this
in the morning?

1034
00:39:20,205 --> 00:39:24,407
No, Jessica, we can't.

1035
00:39:25,025 --> 00:39:29,361
Leonard Bailey's
execution date's been set,

1036
00:39:29,396 --> 00:39:33,264
and I don't know how to tell
a man that he's going to die.

1037
00:39:33,300 --> 00:39:36,201
<i>[dark music]</i>

1038
00:39:36,236 --> 00:39:39,571
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1039
00:39:39,777 --> 00:39:41,088
You know,
I always knew that Jill and I

1040
00:39:41,112 --> 00:39:43,112
were from two
different worlds.

1041
00:39:45,349 --> 00:39:48,851
And she was a Sutter,
and I was just--

1043
00:39:49,987 --> 00:39:51,954
and didn't have much else?

1044
00:39:54,191 --> 00:39:55,435
Figured it was only
a matter of time

1045
00:39:55,459 --> 00:39:58,460
before she came to her senses,

1046
00:39:58,496 --> 00:40:00,629
but she never did.

1047
00:40:00,907 --> 00:40:04,175
Well, let me guess,
William never accepted it.

1048
00:40:04,210 --> 00:40:06,043
No.

1049
00:40:06,078 --> 00:40:08,779
So when he asked me
to develop that algorithm,

1050
00:40:08,815 --> 00:40:12,817
I thought,
"This is my chance."

1051
00:40:12,852 --> 00:40:16,620
And when I gave it to him,
he acted so proud.

1052
00:40:16,656 --> 00:40:20,024
Started calling me
his genius son-in-law.

1053
00:40:20,059 --> 00:40:21,837
But I was really just
the world's biggest sucker,

1054
00:40:21,861 --> 00:40:24,028
because I let that son
of a bitch get one over on me,

1055
00:40:24,063 --> 00:40:26,530
and I'll regret it
for the rest of my life.

1056
00:40:28,868 --> 00:40:33,137
What if you could get
one over on him?

1057
00:40:33,172 --> 00:40:36,173
What are you talking about?

1058
00:40:37,610 --> 00:40:39,476
You said yourself,
they offered you a deal.

1059
00:40:39,512 --> 00:40:41,445
I bet they'd still take it.

1060
00:40:41,480 --> 00:40:44,515
No way. If I give them him,
they go after her.

1061
00:40:44,550 --> 00:40:47,318
Not if you get them
to give Jill immunity first.

1062
00:40:47,353 --> 00:40:48,452
- No.
- Kevin, you have to--

1063
00:40:48,487 --> 00:40:51,155
It's too big a risk,

1064
00:40:51,190 --> 00:40:52,601
and you're
my father-in-law's lawyer.

1065
00:40:52,625 --> 00:40:53,635
You can't even be
saying this to me.

1066
00:40:53,659 --> 00:40:54,692
I am nobody's lawyer.

1067
00:40:54,727 --> 00:40:56,227
I am your friend,
and I am saying--

1068
00:40:56,262 --> 00:40:58,662
Well, my answer's no,
and I want your word, right now,

1069
00:40:58,698 --> 00:41:00,275
that you won't tell anyone
what I told you.

1070
00:41:00,299 --> 00:41:02,010
- Kevin, please, you're not--
- Mike, I'm serious.

1071
00:41:02,034 --> 00:41:05,936
No one can ever know anything
about what I told you.

1072
00:41:05,972 --> 00:41:09,240
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1073
00:41:09,275 --> 00:41:11,709
You have my word.

1074
00:41:11,744 --> 00:41:17,748
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1075
00:41:19,527 --> 00:41:23,396
Did I ever tell you
my mother was a teacher?

1076
00:41:23,431 --> 00:41:26,732
First grade.

1077
00:41:26,768 --> 00:41:28,668
Everybody always said she was
the best teacher

1078
00:41:28,703 --> 00:41:30,937
their kid ever had.

1079
00:41:30,972 --> 00:41:34,307
She loved it.

1080
00:41:34,342 --> 00:41:37,877
She also always dreamed of
seeing Spain when she retired.

1081
00:41:39,380 --> 00:41:42,315
That was supposed
to be six years ago,

1082
00:41:42,350 --> 00:41:43,950
but then the state
teacher's pension fund

1083
00:41:43,985 --> 00:41:48,387
decided to invest its money
with William Sutter.

1084
00:41:51,659 --> 00:41:55,761
She died last year,
still working.

1085
00:41:55,797 --> 00:41:57,107
And every year,
I tried to pay for her trip,

1086
00:41:57,131 --> 00:41:59,165
but she just wouldn't let me.

1087
00:41:59,200 --> 00:42:01,434
Sean, why are you
telling me this?

1088
00:42:01,469 --> 00:42:03,769
Because a judge decided
to rule on your motion

1089
00:42:03,805 --> 00:42:06,272
to dismiss after all.

1090
00:42:06,307 --> 00:42:08,274
Which means
we're out of time,

1091
00:42:08,309 --> 00:42:13,045
and you didn't just come here
to tell me about your mother.

1092
00:42:13,081 --> 00:42:14,947
No.

1093
00:42:14,983 --> 00:42:18,150
I came here to ask
for that trading program.

1094
00:42:18,186 --> 00:42:21,354
<i>♪ ♪</i>

